1
00:02:34,580 --> 00:02:36,935
OK! I know how to handle your type.

2
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:22,337
Well, old faithful,
that's your shooting for the day.

3
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:24,970
If we haven't rung up
at least two rabbits,

4
00:03:25,140 --> 00:03:27,734
we deserve to go home empty-handed.

5
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:31,813
Yeah, still, blessed are they
who expect nothing.

6
00:03:31,980 --> 00:03:34,016
For they shall not be disappointed.

7
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:39,698
Mm. Fewer things in life give a man
more pleasure than hunting.

8
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:42,249
It satisfies his primitive nature,

9
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:46,174
striding through the woods,
picking up his kill.

10
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:48,615
Well, come on, old faithful.

11
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:52,614
There's plump rabbits
waiting for the frying pan.

12
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:20,137
If this can had four legs and a tail,
we'd be eating it tonight.

13
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:23,810
Clean through the heart.

14
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,016
For rice cake! I've done him in.

15
00:04:58,180 --> 00:05:00,171
Cor.

16
00:05:01,580 --> 00:05:05,971
A harmless pot-shot at a rabbit
and I'm a murderer, a killer.

17
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:08,813
Mother always said
I'd come to a bad end.

18
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:11,540
What in Hades were you doing here
anyway?

19
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:16,499
I can't say that I've seen you
around here before.

20
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:21,529
No. If you're going to get yourself
shot, do it where you're known.

21
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,416
"Mr Harry Worp,

22
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:35,698
87 Maple Avenue,
Boston, Massachusetts. "

23
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:39,409
Worp, you're a long way from home.

24
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:42,333
With the looks of it, you won't
get back for Christmas, now.

25
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:47,176
We're going to have a cold,
hard winter.

26
00:05:47,340 --> 00:05:50,810
Mm. You might keep here a long time,
an awful long time.

27
00:05:50,980 --> 00:05:52,971
Too long for me, Harry.

28
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:55,017
Yes.

29
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,617
Captain Wiles?

30
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:10,617
Yes, ma'am?

31
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:16,051
What seems to be the trouble,
Captain?

32
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:20,691
It's what you might call
an unavoidable accident.

33
00:06:20,860 --> 00:06:24,170
- He's dead.
- Yes.

34
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:30,497
I would say that he was. Of course,
that's an unprofessional opinion.

35
00:06:30,660 --> 00:06:33,970
Yeah. Did you...
did you know him, Miss Gravely?

36
00:06:34,140 --> 00:06:38,053
- No. Doesn't live around here.
- Well, he died around here.

37
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:41,132
- That's what counts now.
- Embarrassing.

38
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:44,849
What do you plan to do with him,
Captain?

39
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:49,810
Miss Gravely, without cutting the hem
off truth's garment,

40
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:52,972
I'm gonna hide him, cover him up,

41
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:55,131
forget him.

42
00:06:57,860 --> 00:07:00,738
Are you never going to inform
the police, Captain?

43
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:04,210
No. Forget you saw me, Miss Gravely.

44
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:07,417
Chase it out of your mind, for
heaven's sake, it was an accident.

45
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:11,414
He was poking around the clearing
and I thought he was a rabbit.

46
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:15,209
It was a human error.
Ah, now, please, don't...

47
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:18,577
Don't say anything to anybody,
Miss Gravely.

48
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:22,410
Do as you think best, Captain.

49
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:25,572
I'm sure you must have met
many similar situations

50
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,776
in your travels in foreign lands.

51
00:07:27,940 --> 00:07:31,216
- Yeah, I've seen much worse things.
- I certainly won't say anything.

52
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:33,769
Much worse things.
I remember when I was on the Orinoco.

53
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:37,137
We had a Turk, a great, big Turk,
running amuck with a machete -

54
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:40,815
Captain, if I were going to hide
an accident, I shouldn't delay.

55
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:44,973
Oh. Oh.
You're right as rain, Miss Gravely.

56
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:48,928
Yes. You know something?
I'm glad I met you today.

57
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:51,853
I feel better for telling someone
as warm,

58
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:55,849
tender, understanding as yourself.

59
00:07:56,020 --> 00:08:00,013
Well, on the contrary, Captain. It...

60
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:02,216
It...

61
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:05,178
I'm certainly glad
if I helped you, Captain.

62
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:08,491
Perhaps you would care to come over
for some blueberry muffins

63
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:11,333
and coffee later on,
high-bush blueberries?

64
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:14,253
Ah, well. This is certainly something
of an interesting surprise.

65
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:16,980
- And maybe some elderberry wine.
- Oh!

66
00:08:17,420 --> 00:08:20,810
After all, we've been neighbours
for nearly three years now and...

67
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,971
we've never exchanged social calls.

68
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:25,893
You're right.
It's high time I paid a call.

69
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:29,530
- What time?
- Oh, say, early this afternoon.

70
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,375
I'll be there with a clean shirt
and a hungry face.

71
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:34,655
Do that.

72
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:39,457
You better be going now. Don't want
to be an accessory after the fact.

73
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:44,250
You are a considerate man,
Captain Wiles.

74
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,895
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

75
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,929
We're almost there, Mommy!

76
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:15,291
Here he is, Mommy. Here he is.

77
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:19,934
- What did I tell ya, Mommy?
- Don't touch it, Arnie.

78
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:24,696
- There he is.
- No. It can't be! Harry!

79
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:29,294
Harry, thank Providence,
the last of Harry.

80
00:09:29,460 --> 00:09:32,770
- Who's Providence, Mommy?
- A very good friend.

81
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:35,090
- Don't you know who it is?
- You said Harry.

82
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:38,650
- Can't you remember, Arnie?
- Why don't he get up and move?

83
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:40,811
He's asleep.

84
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:44,370
He's in a deep sleep,
a deep, wonderful sleep.

85
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:46,531
How'd he hurt his head?

86
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,691
Putting it where it wasn't wanted,
would be my guess.

87
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:51,658
- Will it get better?
- Not if we're lucky.

88
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:55,771
Let's run home
and I'll make you some lemonade.

89
00:09:55,940 --> 00:09:58,977
Will lemonade put me in a wonderful,
deep, deep sleep, Mommy?

90
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,131
No, Arnie, but it's better
than no lemonade.

91
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:04,895
- I don't understand that.
- Never mind. Forget you saw him.

92
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:07,972
- Is there a special way to forget?
- Just think of something else.

93
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:11,689
- I'll try not to see him tomorrow.
- That's a good boy, Arnie.

94
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:14,658
Now, let's run home
and get that lemonade.

95
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:18,859
She won't care what I do with him.

96
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,575
Couldn't have had more people here
if I'd sold tickets.

97
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:39,940
What's the big attraction, I wonder?

98
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:09,218
This could turn out to be
the luckiest day of my life.

99
00:11:18,980 --> 00:11:22,734
I'll just wait till the whole world
comes to pay their last respects.

100
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:26,017
Sooner or later one of them has
to turn out to be the Deputy Sheriff.

